      <biogHist id="md5-c2a0aa7679a28eb1d167807b150f948e">
        <p>Author, Journalist, Antique dealer, 1879-1963.  Gertude Balmer Watt, journalist and antique dealer, was the author of A Woman in the West (1907), Town and Trail (1908) and numerous columns and reviews for newspapers in the Edmonton area.  She was a charter member of the Canadian Women's Press Club, which was organized in 1904.  Mrs. Watt was the wife of editor Arthur Balmer Watt and the mother of author Frederick Balmer Watt.</p>
      </biogHist>
